ActMotor Vehicle Safety Act
PrecisRegulations Amending the MOTOR VEHICLE SAFETY REGULATIONS (LOCKING AND IMMOBILIZATION SYSTEMS) by requiring that most vehicles, such as passenger cars, mini-vans, SUVs, pick-up trucks and three-wheeled vehicles, be equipped with anti-theft immobilization devices, effective September 1, 2007.
